description:
Z spec audit finding: handle_pre_compact() in hooks.py is implemented, but no PreCompact hook exists in hooks.json. Session conversations are lost on compaction.

## Current State
- handle_pre_compact() exists in hooks.py — reads transcript JSONL, extracts user/assistant messages (500KB limit), ingests into session-notes collection
- hooks.json has NO PreCompact entry
- Result: context compaction destroys conversation history with no capture

## Fix
Add to hooks.json:
{
  'PreCompact': [{
    'hooks': [{
      'type': 'command',
      'command': '${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks/pre-compact.sh',
      'async': true
    }]
  }]
}

Create hooks/pre-compact.sh that calls: quarry hooks pre-compact < /dev/stdin

## Z Spec Reference
docs/claude-code-quarry.tex, CaptureBeforeCompact operation.
The compactionSaved flag tracks whether capture occurred before each compaction.
